PortSystem          1.0
PortGroup           eda-github 1.0
name                netlistsvg
version             1.0.2
revision            0

categories          cad graphics
license             MIT
maintainers         {icanalytica.com:degnan @bpdegnan} openmaintainer
supported_archs     noarch
platforms           any

description         draws SVG schematics from Yosys JSON netlists
long_description    netlistsvg renders SVG schematics from the JSON netlists \
                    that yosys emits via write_json. Required by the SkyWater \
                    sky130 PDK build to draw standard-cell schematics. This \
                    port installs from the npm registry tarball with every \
                    runtime dependency vendored as a pinned, checksummed \
                    distfile, so the build is fully offline and never runs npm.

homepage            https://github.com/nturley/netlistsvg

# ============================================================================
# npm dependency vendoring
#
# The dependency tree resolved by npm is FLAT (no nested node_modules), so
# each dep tarball is simply extracted into node_modules/<name> and node's
# directory-walking resolver finds everything. No npm at build or run time.
#
# Note the @types/* tarballs do not use "package/" as their root directory
# (DefinitelyTyped uses the package name), hence --strip-components=1 rather
# than relying on a fixed root name.
#
# To regenerate on a version bump: in an empty dir run
#   npm install --package-lock-only --ignore-scripts netlistsvg@<ver>
# confirm no lockfile key contains "node_modules" twice (tree still flat),
# then download each "resolved" tarball and record sha256 + size below.
#
# Each entry: {name filename sha256 size}
# ============================================================================
